-- Sierra Leone Central Bank Sells $1 Million at Currency Auction
-- B y   S i l a s   G b a n d i a
-- 2012-03-30T08:09:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/sierra-leone-central-bank-sells-1-million-at-currency-auction.html
The Bank of Sierra Leone sold $1
million in a foreign exchange auction on March 28, at an
exchange rate of 4,328.69 leones per dollar, the central bank
said on its website. Its next auction of $1 million is due on
April 4.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Silas Gbandia in Freetown at 
 sgbandia@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
